                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1251">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/394.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Teoloyucan</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 12, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s August 8. General Carranza is without advices in this matter up to
                    this time. He has asked authorities at Tampico for information and
                    explanation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
